The paper also mentions the use of graph traversal in processing graph-based data, which falls under the category of algorithms and computational complexity, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical and applied aspects of graph research, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
